30/11/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Valentin Inzko said on Monday (November 29th) that BiH could get EU candidate status in four to five years. 
He pointed out that the EU's decision to scrap visa requirements for Bosnian citizens confirmed that the country has European prospects. 
Inzko added that political leaders can implement necessary reforms when they are united and focused on the EU agenda. 
(Srna, Fena, BHRT, Nezavisne Novine - 29/11/10)
